review_blob:
Aroma: Caramel, chocolate, nuts with a hint of raisins and dates.
Appearance: Amber red sparkling with minimal tan head.
Taste: Medium sweet low bitterness best temp to drink is 50 ( about 10 to 15 min out of the fridge.
Palate: Full flavor strong delightful finish. 
Overall: The best Belgium Triple out there.
